Name: inflammatory myofibroblastic tumor
Definition: A mesenchymal cell neoplasm that has_material_basis_in myofibroblastic cells admixed with inflammatory cells.

Name: parachordoma
Definition: A cell type benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in mesothelium.

Name: ossifying fibromyxoid tumor
Definition: A cell type benign neoplasm that is composed_of glandular and fibrous tissues

Name: amyloid tumor
Definition: A breast carcinoma that is characterized by an individual having breast cancer in both breasts

Name: congenital granular cell tumor
Definition: A uterine corpus cancer that has_material_basis_in endometrial stroma and smooth muscle cells.

Name: nonossifying fibromyxoid tumor
Definition: A uterine corpus cancer that has_material_basis_in endometrial stroma and smooth muscle cells.
